summary:
The Security Council:

Reaffirms demand to prevent supply of arms to armed groups in DRC; 
Welcomes recommendations on MONUC; 
Requests MONUC to inspect cargo and seize/collect arms violating embargo; 
Condemns illegal exploitation of natural resources; 
Urges states to end these activities; 
Establishes Committee to monitor implementation of arms embargo and gather information on violations; 
 Committee to seek information from states, examine alleged violations, and take action.
The Security Council,

8. Decides to establish, in accordance with rule 28 of its provisional rules of procedure, a Committee, consisting of all members of the Council, to be chaired by the representative of Chile, to carry out the following tasks:
(a) To monitor the implementation of the measures imposed by paragraph 20 of resolution 1493;
(b) To gather information on entities reported to be engaged in such violations, as well as aircraft or other vehicles used;
(c) To present regular reports to the Council on its work, with its observations and recommendations;
(d) To consider the lists referred to hereafter in paragraph 10 (g) with a view to submitting recommendations to the Council;
(e) To receive notifications in advance from States made under paragraph 21 of resolution 1493;
9. Requests all States to report to the Committee within sixty days on the actions they have taken to implement the measures imposed by paragraph 20 of resolution 1493;
10. Requests the Secretary-General to create, within thirty days, a group of experts consisting of no more than four members, with the following mandate:
(a) To examine and analyse information gathered by MONUC;
(b) To gather and analyse information on flows of arms and related materiel;
(c) To consider and recommend ways of improving the capabilities of States to ensure the measures imposed by paragraph 20 of resolution 1493 are effectively implemented;
(d) To report to the Council in writing before 15 July 2004;
(e) To keep the Committee frequently updated on its activities;
(f) To exchange with MONUC information that might be of use;
(g) To provide the Committee with a list, with supporting evidence, of those found to have violated the measures imposed by paragraph 20 of resolution 1493;
11. Requests the Special Representative of the Secretary-General to communicate information gathered by MONUC to the Security Council;
